00044   /// A 32 bit bit-field for GNSS measurement associated flags (all are boolean indicators).
00045   struct GNSS_structFlagsBitField
00046   {
00047     unsigned isActive:1;              //!< This flag indicates that the channel is active for use. If this is not set, no other flags are valid for use.
00048     unsigned isCodeLocked:1;          //!< Indicates if the code tracking is locked.
00049     unsigned isPhaseLocked:1;         //!< Indicates if the phase tracking is locked.
00050     unsigned isParityValid:1;         //!< Indicates if the phase parity if valid.      
00051     unsigned isPsrValid:1;            //!< Indicates if the pseudorange valid for use.
00052     unsigned isAdrValid:1;            //!< Indicates if the ADR is valid for use.
00053     unsigned isDopplerValid:1;        //!< Indicates if the Doppler if valid for use.
00054     unsigned isGrouped:1;             //!< Indicates if this channel has another associated channel. eg. L1 and L2 measurements.
00055     unsigned isAutoAssigned:1;        //!< Indicates if the channel was receiver assigned (otherwise, the user forced this channel assignment).
00056     unsigned isCarrierSmoothed:1;     //!< Indicates if the pseudorange has carrier smoothing enabled.
00057     unsigned isEphemerisValid:1;      //!< Indicates if this channel has valid associated ephemeris information. 
00058     unsigned isAlmanacValid:1;        //!< Indicates if this channel has valid associated almanac information.
00059     unsigned isAboveElevationMask:1;  //!< Indicates if the satellite tracked is above the elevation mask.    
00060     unsigned isAboveCNoMask:1;        //!< Indciates if the channel's C/No is above a threshold value.
00061     unsigned isAboveLockTimeMask:1;   //!< Indicates if the channel's locktime is above a treshold value.
00062     unsigned isNotUserRejected:1;     //!< Indicates if the user has not forced the rejection of this channel or PRN.
00063     unsigned isNotPsrRejected:1;      //!< Indicates if the pseudorange was not rejetced (ie Fault Detection and Exclusion).
00064     unsigned isNotAdrRejected:1;      //!< Indicates if the ADR was not rejetced (ie Fault Detection and Exclusion).
00065     unsigned isNotDopplerRejected:1;  //!< Indicates if the Doppler was not rejected (ie Fault Detection and Exclusion).
00066     unsigned isNoCycleSlipDetected:1; //!< Indicates that no cycle slip has occurred at this epoch.
00067     unsigned isUsedInPosSolution:1;   //!< Indicates if some part (pseudorange) of this channel's measurement was used in the position solution.
00068     unsigned isUsedInVelSolution:1;   //!< Indicates if some part (Doppler) of this channel's measurement was used in the velocity solution.
00069     unsigned isAdrUsedInSolution:1;   //!< Indicates if the the ADR is used in the solution.
00070 
00071     unsigned isDifferentialPsrAvailable:1;     //!< Indicates if a matching pseudrange observation is available from another receiver.
00072     unsigned isDifferentialDopplerAvailable:1; //!< Indicates if a matching Doppler observation is available from another receiver.
00073     unsigned isDifferentialAdrAvailable:1;     //!< Indicates if a matching ADR observation is available from another receiver.
00074     
00075     unsigned useTropoCorrection:1;         //!< Indicates that the tropospheric correction should be applied.
00076     unsigned useBroadcastIonoCorrection:1; //!< Indicates that the broadcast ionospheric correction should be applied.
00077       
00078     unsigned isTimeDifferntialPsrAvailable:1;
00079     unsigned isTimeDifferntialDopplerAvailable:1;
00080 
00081     unsigned reserved:2;
00082   };

00187   /// \brief    Measurement data associated with a single receiver measurement channel.
00188   ///
00189   /// This struct is 4 and 8 byte struct member packing compatible.
00190   struct GNSS_structMeasurement
00191   {
00192     unsigned short            channel;  //!< The channel number associated with this measurement.
00193     unsigned short            id;       //!< The unique id for this channel (eg PRN for GPS).    
00194     GNSS_enumSystem           system;   //!< The satellite system associated with this channel.
00195     GNSS_enumCodeType         codeType; //!< The code type for this channel.
00196     GNSS_enumFrequency        freqType; //!< The frequency type for this channel.
00197     GNSS_structFlagsBitField  flags;    //!< The flags associated with this channel. ie Validity flags, etc.
00198 
00199     unsigned short week;  //!< The measurement gps week (at 'transmit' time) [weeks].
00200     double   tow;         //!< The measurement gps time of week (at 'transmit' time) [s].
00201     
00202     // The actual measurements.
00203     double   psr;               //!< The pseudorange measurement [m].
00204     double   adr;               //!< The carrier phase or accumulated Doppler range measurement [cycles].
00205     float    doppler;           //!< The Doppler measurement for this channel [Hz].
00206     float    cno;               //!< The carrier to noise density ratio for this channel [dB-Hz]
00207     float    locktime;          //!< The number of seconds of continous phase tracking (no known cycle slips) [s].
00208     
00209     // The variance information associated with the actual measurements.
00210     float    stdev_psr;         //!< The estimated pseudorange measurement standard deviation [m].
00211     float    stdev_adr;         //!< The estimated accumulated Doppler range measurement standard deviation [cycles].
00212     float    stdev_doppler;     //!< The estimated Doppler measurement standard deviation [Hz].
00213 
00214     // Derived information.
00215     double   psr_misclosure;    //!< The measured psr minus the computed psr estimate [m].
00216     double   doppler_misclosure;//!< The measured Doppler minus the computed Doppler estimate [m].
00217     double   range;             //!< The best estimate of the geometric range between the antenna and the satellite [m].
00218     double   rangerate;         //!< The best estimate of the geometric range rate between the antenna and the satellite [m/s].
00219     double   psr_smoothed;      //!< The carrier smoothed pseudorange if available [m].
00220     double   psr_predicted;     //!< The predicted pseudorange based on the satellite position, user position, and current clock offset [m].
00221     double   ambiguity;         //!< The estimated integer component of the adr. This may be the single or double differenced ambiguity [].
00222     float    doppler_predicted; //!< The predicted Doppler based on user position, velocity, satellite position, velocity and clock rate [Hz].
00223     float    azimuthRads;       //!< The associated satellite azimuth for this channel [rad].
00224     float    elevationRads;     //!< The associated satellite elevation for this channel  [rad].
00225     
00226 
00227     short index_differential;      //!< The channel index of a matching differential observation. -1 means there is no matching channel.
00228     short index_time_differential; //!< The channel index of a matching time differential observation. -1 means there is no matching channel.
00229   short index_between_satellite_differential; //!< The channel index for between satellite difference of the satellite that is substracted from this one. -1 means there is no matching channel.
00230     int    index_differential_adr;  //!< The channel index of a matching differential observation. -1 means there is no matching channel.
00231     int    index_ambiguity_state;   //!< The index into the state vector for this ambiguity state. -1 not estimated.
00232     double adr_misclosure;          //!< The measured ADR minus the computed ADR estimate [m]. This is likely a differential quantity.
00233     
00234     double H_p[3]; //!< The design matrix row relating the pseudorange measurements to the position solution. dP/d(lat), dP/d(lon), dP/d(hgt).
00235     double H_v[3]; //!< The design matrix row relating the Doppler measurements to the velocity solution. dD/d(lat), dD/d(lon), dD/d(hgt).
00236 
00237     GNSS_structCorrections  corrections; //!< The corrections associated with this channel.
00238     GNSS_structResiduals    residuals;   //!< The post-adjustment (filtering) measurement residual associated with this channel.
00239 
00240     GNSS_structSatellitePVT satellite;  //!< Each channel has an associated satellite pvt struct evaluated at the transmit time.
00241   };
